<span id="freeTextContainer10313439596648676067">I wasn’t sure what to think when I read the synopsis because this was a different type of audiobook/book than my norm. I think it was beautifully written, but referring to any of these as a “short story” didn’t fit with what I listened to. These were more like someone’s thoughts, but not like journal entries either. Because of this, there were times throughout listening when I found myself distracted and had a hard time staying focused. <br/><br/>I wasn&apos;t a fan of the narrator. Maybe if someone else had r</span>
  <span id="freeText10313439596648676067" style="display:none">I wasn’t sure what to think when I read the synopsis because this was a different type of audiobook/book than my norm. I think it was beautifully written, but referring to any of these as a “short story” didn’t fit with what I listened to. These were more like someone’s thoughts, but not like journal entries either. Because of this, there were times throughout listening when I found myself distracted and had a hard time staying focused. <br /><br />I wasn't a fan of the narrator. Maybe if someone else had read this, I would have liked it more/held my attention better. But the narrator was unnatural sounding as he read. He sounded robotic and/or nasally like perhaps something was wrong with his microphone. <br /><br />I received a free audiobook code in exchange for an honest review.</span>
